Asking the Cubs for free stuff on Twitter is asking to be trolled.
Don’t believe me? Ask Dakota Turner.
The fan tweeted at the Cubs during Sunday’s NLCS Game 2 asking for a Kyle Schwarber jersey. He got a deep burn instead.
@Cubs can I have a Kyle Shwarber jersey now?
— Dakota Turner (@Dakotaturner21) October 19, 2015
@Dakotaturner21 DM us your info.
— Chicago Cubs (@Cubs) October 19, 2015
@Cubs I can't DM you
— Dakota Turner (@Dakotaturner21) October 19, 2015
@Dakotaturner21 Oh. That's unfortunate.
— Chicago Cubs (@Cubs) October 19, 2015
It’s easy to understand why the fan was asking for a Schwarber jersey. The rookie has been incredible this postseason, batting .421 with four home runs.
